{{distinguish|Aeromobil|airmobile}} '''AeroMobile Communications Limited''' is a registered mobile network operator for the aviation industry and is based in the UK. It provides technology and services that allow the safe use of passengers' own mobile phones while inflight. A subsidiary of [[Panasonic]] Avionics Corporation <ref>{{cite web|last=Ian|first=Mansfield|title=Panasonic Takes Majority Stake in AeroMobile|url=http://www.cellular-news.com/story/53684.php|work=Cellular News |accessdate=27 Mar 2012}}</ref> its services are often installed alongside Panasonic's Wi-Fi network and can be installed either at the point of aircraft manufacture or retro-fitted across both [[Airbus]] and [[Boeing]] aircraft. Panasonic Avionic's Wi-Fi network and AeroMobile's mobile phone network are complimentary services and provide passengers with a choice of inflight connectivity options.
Since launching the service in March 2008, over 40 million passengers have connected to the network<ref>{{cite web|title=More Than Three-Quarters Of Brits Use Their Mobile Phones Abroad|url=http://www.aeromobile.net/pressinfo/more-than-three-quarters-of-brits-use-their-mobile-phones-abroad/ |publisher=Aeromobile PR|accessdate=May 23, 2013}}</ref><ref name=aero>{{cite web|title=About AeroMobile |url=http://www.aeromobile.net/about-us/ |publisher=aeromobile.net |accessdate=1 November 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131102175557/http://www.aeromobile.net/about-us/ |archivedate=2 November 2013 }}</ref><ref name=inflight>{{cite web|title=Aer Lingus Launches InFlight Mobile Services With AeroMobile |url=http://airfax.com/blog/index.php/tag/aeromobile/ |publisher=airfax.com/blog/index.php |accessdate=1 November 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141018111359/http://airfax.com/blog/index.php/tag/aeromobile/ |archivedate=18 October 2014 }}</ref><ref name=inflight1>{{cite web|title=Aeromobile provides Singapore Airlines with in-flight Wi-Fi and GSM |url=http://www.wireless-mag.com/News/26728/Aeromobile_provides_Singapore_Airlines_with_in-flight_Wi-Fi_and_GSM.aspx|publisher=aircraftinteriorsinternational.com/|accessdate=1 November 2013}}</ref><ref name=uk>{{cite web|title=AeroMobile research reveals UK travellers mobile phone habits |url=http://www.aircraftinteriorsinternational.com/news.php?NewsID=49308|publisher=aircraftinteriorsinternational.com|accessdate=1 November 2013}}</ref> and AeroMobile now has over 20 airline partners offering passengers inflight voice, SMS and data services on selected, connected flights. Airline partners include [[Emirates (airline)|Emirates]], [[Etihad Airways|Etihad]], [[KLM]], [[Lufthansa]], [[Scandinavian Airlines|SAS]], [[Virgin Atlantic]], [[Singapore Airlines]], [[Cathay Pacific]] and [[Turkish Airlines]].
In December 2015 AeroMobile launched the world's first 3.5G inflight mobile network with [[Air Berlin]].<ref name=aero3g>{{cite web|title=AeroMobile launches world's first inflight 3.5G network |url=http://www.aeromobile.net/pressinfo/aeromobile-launches-worlds-first-inflight-3g-service/}}</ref> The 3.5G network provides passengers with a substantial increase in data speeds, faster browsing and quicker posts.
