[[File:Kaplanturbine als Denkmal.jpg|thumbnail|right|300px|Litostroj [[Kaplan turbine]]]] '''Litostroj''' is a [[Slovenia]]n [[Heavy industry|heavy machinery]] [[Manufacturing|manufacturer]] based in [[Ljubljana]]. Its products include mainly [[water turbine]]s for [[hydroelectric powerplant]]s. Most of production is [[export]]ed. It provided around 8000 MW of installed power worldwide. Around 150 of them are pumped storage. It has also designed around 1200 large [[Crane (machine)|cranes]]. They also manufacture forging and pressing machines.
Its name is derived from {{lang|sl|<u>Li</u>varna in <u>to</u>varna <u>stroj</u>ev}}, meaning "Foundry and Machine Factory" in Slovene.<ref>{{cite article |url=http://www.fm-kp.si/zalozba/ISBN/978-961-266-033-8/prispevki/Rot%20Tom.pdf |title=Organizacijska kultura ob prestrukturiranju družbe |language=Slovenian |trans-title=The Organisational Culture at the Restructuring of a Company |first=Tom |last=Rot | date=November 2009 |work=Zbornik 6. študentske konference Fakultete za management Koper |page=821 |publisher=Faculty of Management, University of Koper}}</ref> [[Litostroj Street]] ({{lang|sl|Litostrojska cesta}}) in Ljubljana is named after the company.
