'''Test 219''' was a [[nuclear test]] conducted by the [[Soviet Union]] in the atmosphere via [[ICBM]]. The test was performed on December 24, 1962 over the [[Novaya Zemlya]] test range. It was a thermonuclear fusion bomb with a yield of about 24.2 megatons and a destruction radius of about six miles, making it the second largest thermonuclear explosion in history behind [[Tsar Bomba]].<ref>Nuclear Weapons Archive http://nuclearweaponarchive.org/Russia/Sovatmtest.html</ref>

